<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="37">
The correct name for this taxon at the rank of species has been the source of confusion. With the earlier name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dougl. ex Benth" authorityYear="1846" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Penstemon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Penstemon suffruticosus" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suffruticosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">Penstemon suffruticosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Douglas ex Benth. blocking transfer of A. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Gray’s">Gray's</normalizedToken>
varietal epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dougl. ex Benth" authorityYear="1846" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Penstemon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="suffruticosus" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suffruticosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">suffruticosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at the rank of species, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/2478562" author="Rydberg, PA" journalOrPublisher="Club" pageId="5" pageNumber="38" pagination="499 - 513" refId="B7" refString="Rydberg, PA, 1901. Studies on the Rocky Mountain flora.-VI. Bull. Torrey Bot. Club 28: 499 - 513, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/2478562" title="Studies on the Rocky Mountain flora. - VI. Bull. Torrey Bot." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/2478562" volume="28" year="1901">Rydberg (1901)</bibRefCitation>
published 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. suffrutescens" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="species" species="suffrutescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">P. suffrutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in an attempt to provide a substitute. However, in doing so, he flagged 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. suffrutescens" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="species" species="suffrutescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">P. suffrutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a new species (sp. nov.). He also provided a brief diagnosis and cited a specimen (
<collectingCountry name="United States of America">USA</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingRegion country="United States of America" name="Colorado">Colorado</collectingRegion>
. Ridgway, woods, altitude 
<quantity metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.286" unit="ft" value="7500.0">7500 ft</quantity>
, 
<date value="1895-06-20">20 Jun 1895</date>
, F. Tweedy 170; 
<typeStatus>holotype</typeStatus>
: NY, NY00130526 [NY website image]) different from that of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Gray’s">Gray's</normalizedToken>
type for 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. caespitosus subsp. var. var. suffruticosus" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="variety" species="caespitosus" subSpecies="var." variety="suffruticosus">P. caespitosus var. suffruticosus</taxonomicName>
. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Rydberg’s">Rydberg's</normalizedToken>
name must be considered a validly published species name-not an avowed substitute for 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Gray’s">Gray's</normalizedToken>
name. As noted by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/2806680" author="Holmgren, NH" journalOrPublisher="Brittonia" pageId="5" pageNumber="38" pagination="104 - 107" refId="B2" refString="Holmgren, NH, 1979. Nomenclatural changes in some Intermountain penstemons. Brittonia 31: 104 - 107, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/2806680" title="Nomenclatural changes in some Intermountain penstemons." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/2806680" volume="31" year="1979">Holmgren (1979)</bibRefCitation>
, the specimen cited by Rydberg is referable to 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. crandallii" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="species" species="crandallii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">P. crandallii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, where 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. suffrutescens" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="species" species="suffrutescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">P. suffrutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must be placed as a synonym.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="37">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1086/328257" author="Nelson, A" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Rocky Mountain Herbarium" pageId="5" pageNumber="38" pagination="21 - 35" refId="B5" refString="Nelson, A, 1902. . Contributions from the Rocky Mountain Herbarium III: 21 - 35, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1086/328257" url="https://doi.org/10.1086/328257" volume="III" year="1902">Nelson (1902)</bibRefCitation>
published 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Penstemon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Penstemon xylus" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="xylus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">Penstemon xylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and clearly stated it was a new name (nom. nov.) for 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Gray’s">Gray's</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. caespitosus subsp. var. var. suffruticosus" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="variety" species="caespitosus" subSpecies="var." variety="suffruticosus">P. caespitosus var. suffruticosus</taxonomicName>
. Nelson cited a specimen (
<collectingCountry name="United States of America">USA</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingRegion country="United States of America" name="Colorado">Colorado</collectingRegion>
. Sapinero, 1898, H.N. Wheeler 446 [COLO, COLO00396499 [JSTOR image], NY, NY00130556 [NY website image], RM, RM0004372 [JSTOR image]) that he believed was referable to A. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Gray’s">Gray's</normalizedToken>
concept of 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. caespitosus subsp. var. var. suffruticosus" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="variety" species="caespitosus" subSpecies="var." variety="suffruticosus">P. caespitosus var. suffruticosus</taxonomicName>
. However, it too is referable to 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. crandallii" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="species" species="crandallii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">P. crandallii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/2806680" author="Holmgren, NH" journalOrPublisher="Brittonia" pageId="5" pageNumber="38" pagination="104 - 107" refId="B2" refString="Holmgren, NH, 1979. Nomenclatural changes in some Intermountain penstemons. Brittonia 31: 104 - 107, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/2806680" title="Nomenclatural changes in some Intermountain penstemons." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/2806680" volume="31" year="1979">Holmgren (1979)</bibRefCitation>
, believing that neither 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Rydberg’s">Rydberg's</normalizedToken>
nor 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Nelson’s">Nelson's</normalizedToken>
name could be applied to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Gray’s">Gray's</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. caespitosus subsp. var. var. suffruticosus" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="variety" species="caespitosus" subSpecies="var." variety="suffruticosus">P. caespitosus var. suffruticosus</taxonomicName>
because of the specimens cited by each author, published 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. tusharensis" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="species" species="tusharensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">P. tusharensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as an avowed substitute. In spite of Nelson having cited a specimen that is not referable to 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. caespitosus subsp. var. var. suffruticosus" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="variety" species="caespitosus" subSpecies="var." variety="suffruticosus">P. caespitosus var. suffruticosus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. xylus" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="species" species="xylus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">P. xylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must stand as the avowed substitute for 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. caespitosus subsp. var. var. suffruticosus" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="variety" species="caespitosus" subSpecies="var." variety="suffruticosus">P. caespitosus var. suffruticosus</taxonomicName>
at the rank of species, making 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. tusharensis" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="species" species="tusharensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">P. tusharensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
illegitimate and superfluous.
</paragraph>
